OL,6,FPeter Mossman, from Altrincham, was
OL,7,Fbeing treated for the blood condition
OL,8,Fhaemophilia, when he was infected
OL,9,Fwhile in his 40s.
OL,11,FHe died in 2021, aged 78, after
OL,12,Fspending decades demanding justice for
OL,13,Fvictims affected by the infected blood
OL,14,Fscandal.
OL,16,FSince then, his son Gareth has taken
OL,17,Fup the fight.
